# @btech packages are published to Azure Artifacts feed "btech".
#
# ── CI pipelines ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth is handled automatically by the npmAuthenticate@0 task using
# System.AccessToken. No personal PAT or env var required.
#
# ── Local development ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Install the Azure Artifacts Credential Provider (one-time, per machine):
#   Windows: iex "& { $(irm https://aka.ms/install-artifacts-credprovider.ps1) }"
#   macOS/Linux: sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://aka.ms/install-artifacts-credprovider.sh)"
# Then run: npx vsts-npm-auth -config .npmrc
# This uses your Azure DevOps login — no PAT needed.
#
# ── External consumers (outside buma org) ───────────────────────────────────
# Generate a PAT at https://dev.azure.com/buma/_usersSettings/tokens
# with Packaging (Read) scope, then set: NODE_AUTH_TOKEN=<your-pat>
@btech:registry=https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/buma/_packaging/btech/npm/registry/
//pkgs.dev.azure.com/buma/_packaging/btech/npm/registry/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
//pkgs.dev.azure.com/buma/_packaging/btech/npm/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
